column1: Daily Weather Observations for Mount William (Grampians), Victoria for March 2016
Prepared at 13:04 GMT on Thursday 14 April 2016   IDCJDW3097.201603
Most observations from Mount William, but cloud from Ararat and pressure from Stawell.
Mount William is 1150 m above sea level in the Grampians. Stawell is 28 km to the northeast, so pressure will sometimes be different. Ararat is about 33 km away.
Temperature, humidity, wind and rainfall observations are from Grampians (Mount William) {station 079103}
Cloud observations are from Ararat Prison {station 089085}
Pressure observations are from Stawell Aerodrome {station 079105}
